# That Open Engine Patterns

Follow official patterns from https://github.com/ThatOpen/engine_components

## World Setup

```javascript
const components = new OBC.Components();
const worlds = components.get(OBC.Worlds);
const world = worlds.create();
world.scene = new OBC.SimpleScene(components);
world.scene.setup(); // sets up lights
world.renderer = new OBC.SimpleRenderer(components, container);
world.camera = new OBC.SimpleCamera(components);
components.get(OBC.Grids).create(world);
components.init();
```

## FragmentsManager (required before IfcLoader)

- Init with blob URL worker: fetch `/Worker/worker.mjs` → `URL.createObjectURL(blob)`
- Hook camera updates: `world.camera.controls.addEventListener("update", () => fragments.core.update())`
- Handle camera change: `world.onCameraChanged.add(cam => { for (const [,m] of fragments.list) m.useCamera(cam.three) })`
- Connect models: `fragments.list.onItemSet.add(({ value: model }) => { model.useCamera(cam); scene.add(model.object) })`
- Z-fighting fix: `material.polygonOffset = true` on non-LOD materials

## Highlighter (requires Raycasters first)

```javascript
components.get(OBC.Raycasters).get(world); // MUST be before Highlighter
const highlighter = components.get(OBCF.Highlighter);
highlighter.setup({ world, selectMaterialDefinition: { color, opacity, transparent, renderedFaces } });
```

## Data Structures

- `ModelIdMap` = `Record<string, Set<number>>` (modelId → local IDs)
- Convert GUIDs: `fragments.guidsToModelIdMap(guids)`
- Convert local IDs to GUIDs: `model.getGuidsByLocalIds([...localIds])`

## Disposal

- Use `fragments.core.disposeModel(modelId)` instead of manual `model.dispose()`

## IFC Loading

- Configure WASM: `loader.setup({ autoSetWasm: false, wasm: { path: "/", absolute: true } })`
- Progress: `loader.load(buffer, true, name, { processData: { progressCallback: (pct) => {} } })`
